# Pulumi / Go build artifacts — never committed (Pulumi builds the program at runtime).
/recollect-platform

# Pulumi keeps stack STATE in your configured backend (Pulumi Cloud or a self-managed
# backend), never in the repo. Per-stack config (Pulumi.<stack>.yaml) is created locally by
# `pulumi stack init` + `pulumi config set`; it may hold ENCRYPTED secrets and is intentionally
# left untracked here so real deploy config (account ids, the chosen region, encrypted secrets)
# isn't committed. Commit a Pulumi.<stack>.yaml deliberately only if it contains no secrets.
Pulumi.*.yaml
